column18: They need to know how it will affect people and how it can damage property so that they can make a way to protect people and the property.
column19:
Some hazards are
Lava flow-It can burn everything in it's path
Bombs-They can hit things and cause it to break
Eruption cloud-Can block sunlight for many days which can make it colder.
Ash fall-The ash can fall and cause fires
Pyroclastic Flow- The gases can explode if they are lit

column19: Some of the hazards shown in the graphic shown are the ash fall, bombs, a lava flow, and an eruption cloud. All of these things can cause serious injuries because the ash and eruption clouds can make it difficult to see, and also, the lava and the bombs can injure people because of the hot temperature.

column24: Knowing information about past eruptions can be helpful to scientists because it could show eruption patterns and help them find the cause of some eruptions. With this information they could possibly try to prevent eruptions depending on what the cause was and maybe find a way to reduce the destruction.
column25:
A: A large town -- Houses could be destroyed and people could get hurt.

B: Animals -- They could get very hurt.

C: Agriculture -- Crops will be destroyed which could limit food sources in that area.

D: Airplanes --  Airplanes will be unable to fly, but ones that are already in the air near by can crash hurting thousands of people because pilots will be unable to see ahead.
column26: Yes, because the smoke and ash can still destroy the environment and it will make it difficult for animals to survive in that region.
column27: The high risk area is at the peak of the volcano or in this case the Merapi volcano. The lowest risk is the town farthest away such as Seyegan.
column28: People would know where not to be when a volcano erupts and also rescuers would know what areas to look in to find injured people.
column29: Tephra maps are determined after a volcano erupts but a risk map can easily be developed before a volcano erupts.

column25:
A: A large town -- A large town would be effect by tephra would be having gusts of wind coming torwards buildings smashing windows and more, along with people. It could also damage things such as cars which would slow down life in the city with no cars.
B: Animals -- Animals might not have clean air to breath leading to sickness and possibly death. Another thing could be how the grass might be gone leading to no food.

C: Agriculture -- They're would be no food since all of the plants die keeping people from eating causing extreme hunger.

D: Airplanes --  It could make it hard for the driver to see since the tephra would be in the air and it could bring the plane down. Another thing that could happen is that the gust could get in the jets leading to the airplane crashing.

A: A large town -- The town would be effected by the tephra. The town would definitely have tephra everywhere, like on the roofs and the ground. This would cause their breathing to become sickly and their homes 
B: Animals --  The Animals would have no food because the volcano could have burned the grass sucking out all of the water in side

C: Agriculture -- The crops would die because of the tephra or the lava went onto them. The vegetation would burn and decompose.

D: Airplanes -- Wouldn't be able to fly because the tephra would stop them from traveling and could fog up the windows making the plane crash.
